cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with unsupervised visual representation learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for training, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of smoothing label/prediction distribution is also mentioned, which is related to probability and statistics (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses downstream tasks, which could involve natural language processing (cs.CL).
